          "John Calvin focuses on the providence of God, arguing that this psalm teaches believers that God does not sit idly in heaven but is an active Judge who interposes His power to correct the disorders of the world.",
          "Matthew Henry highlights the stability of God s throne in verse 7, contrasting the vanishing memorials of the wicked (verse 6) with the eternal reign of the Lord. He notes that while cities are destroyed, the Judge remains.",
          "H.C. Leupold points out that the term marvelous works (verse 1) refers to extraordinary acts of God that transcend human ability, specifically the preservation of the covenant people against overwhelming odds.",
