        "title": "Brief Outline",
        "content": "Theme: The triumph of faith over the counsel of fear through the recognition of God's sovereign reign.\n\nI. The Crisis and the Counsel of Fear (1-3)\n\n• David’s initial declaration of trust (1a)\n\n• The advisors’ warning of the archers in the dark (1b-2)\n\n• The rhetorical dilemma of the crumbling foundations (3)\n\nII. The Reality of the Heavenly Reign (4-6)\n\n• The Lord’s location in His temple and throne (4)\n\n• The Lord’s scrutiny and testing of humanity (4b-5)\n\n• The Lord’s judgment of the wicked with fire and brimstone (6)\n\nIII. The Resolution of the Upright (7)\n\n• The character of the Lord as the lover of righteousness (7a)\n\n• The final reward of the beatific vision (7b)"
