          "The Pure Word Incarnate: If God’s words are silver refined seven times, Christ is that Word made flesh. He is the Truth in a world of falsehood.",
          "The Deliverer of the Needy: Verse 5 records God saying, I will arise. This is typological of the Resurrection, where Christ arose to set the oppressed free from the ultimate liar, Satan.",
          "The Rejected Prophet: Just as David’s words of truth were ignored by a flattering generation, Christ’s pure words were met with the proud tongues of the Pharisees."
