        "content": "• Jesus as the Man of Sorrows: Christ perfectly embodied the lament of Psalm 13, experiencing the full weight of the Father’s hidden face during the crucifixion to ensure we would never be permanently forsaken.\n\n• The Sinless Petitioner: Unlike David, who may have been dealing with personal failure, Christ prayed these themes in total righteousness, making His plea for light and life the basis for our own restoration.\n\n• The Victorious Praiser: The transition to praise in verse 6 prefigures Christ’s resurrection joy. As David sings because the Lord has dealt bountifully with him, Christ leads the Great Congregation in praise after His victory over death.",
