        "content": "1. The Truly Innocent Sufferer: While David was relatively innocent compared to Saul, Jesus Christ is the only one who could perfectly say, You have tested my heart... You have found nothing (verse 3). This psalm is the prayer of the Antitypical David.\n\n2. The One Who Kept God’s Paths: In verse 5, David speaks of his steps staying in God’s paths. Christ is the only one who never slipped, fulfilling the law of God perfectly on behalf of His people.\n\n3. The Resurrection Hope: The waking in God’s likeness in verse 15 points forward to the resurrection of Jesus, who is the firstfruits of those who sleep.\n\n4. The Savior of Those Who Trust: Verse 7 calls God the Savior of those who take refuge at His right hand. This is a direct reference to the mediatorial work of Christ, who sits at the right hand of the Father.",
