        "content": "Theme: The Appeal of the Upright Soul for Divine Vindication and the Eternal Hope of God’s Presence.\n\n1. The Protestation of Sincerity (Verses 1-5)\n\nDavid asks for a fair trial based on his integrity and his avoidance of the paths of the destroyer.\n\n2. The Petition for Divine Protection (Verses 6-12)\n\nDavid requests miraculous intervention against arrogant and predatory enemies who surround him.\n\n3. The Prospect of Eternal Satisfaction (Verses 13-15)\n\nDavid contrasts the temporary, earthly portion of the wicked with his own hope of beholding God’s face in the resurrection."
