        "content": "The Talmud in Tamid 31b notes that Psalm 24 was the designated song for the first day of the week in the Temple service, acknowledging God as the Creator who began His work on the first day. Midrash Tehillim connects the opening verses to the foundation of the world upon the waters. Rashi interprets the phrase the earth is the Lords as a reminder that man is merely a tenant on divine property. Later tradition, found in the Midrash, associates verses 7 through 10 with King Solomon attempting to bring the Ark into the newly built Temple; the gates allegedly moved only when David’s name was invoked, signifying God's covenant loyalty to the Davidic line."
