          "Derek Kidner observes the structural tension between the high confidence of the first half and the desperate cries of the second half, suggesting this reflects the reality of the Christian life where faith and struggle coexist.",
          "E.W. Bullinger points out the use of the divine name Jehovah (Yahweh) thirteen times in this Psalm, which underscores the covenantal relationship that forms the basis of David's security.",
          "Alexander Maclaren notes that the land of the living in verse 13 is not merely a place but a state of being in God's presence, contrasting with the spiritual death of the wicked.",
