        "title": "Christ in the Old Testament",
        "content": "Christ is the ultimate Speaker of this Psalm, as He is the One who truly descended into the pit of death and was brought up by the Father.\n\nThe momentary hiding of the Father’s face which David experienced was endured in its totality by Christ on the cross (Matthew 27:46) so that the believer might experience a lifetime of favor.\n\nThe dedication of the house points to Christ as the True Temple. His resurrection was the final dedication of the new and living way into the presence of God.\n\nThe transition from sackcloth to dancing was perfectly realized on Easter morning, when the grave clothes were left behind and the joy of the resurrection began the eternal morning of the New Covenant.",
