        "title": "Christ in the Old Testament",
        "content": "Christ as the Perfect Man: In verse 37, the call to mark the perfect man finds its ultimate fulfillment in Jesus Christ. He is the only truly upright man whose end was peace, despite the temporary triumph of his enemies.\n\nChrist as the Bread of Life: Verse 3 promises that the righteous shall be fed. This points toward the Messiah who provides the true manna from heaven.\n\nChrist the Heir: As the Son of David, Christ is the ultimate heir of the land and the world. Through Him, the meek inherit the earth because they are co-heirs with Christ.\n\nThe Sufferer’s Vindicator: The psalm’s assurance that the Lord will not leave the righteous in the hand of the wicked (verse 33) prefigures the Resurrection, where God vindicated His Son after the injustice of the cross.",
