        "title": "Christ in the Old Testament",
        "content": "The Obedient Servant: Christ is the ultimate fulfillment of the one whose ears are opened and who says, I delight to do your will. Where David’s obedience was partial, Christ’s was perfect.\n\nThe Final Sacrifice: The psalm propheticially points to the end of animal sacrifices. Verse 6 acknowledges that God did not desire bullocks and goats as an end in themselves but as a pointer toward the body prepared for the Messiah.\n\nThe Great Proclaimer: Christ is the one who perfectly declared God's righteousness in the great congregation. His earthly ministry was the ultimate public testimony of God’s truth and salvation.\n\nThe Resurrected King: Conservative typological interpretation views the deliverance from the pit and the miry clay as a type of the Resurrection of Jesus, who was lifted out of the pit of death to be set upon the Rock of eternal life.",
