        "content": "• The Thirsty Savior: On the cross, Jesus cried out, I thirst (John 19:28), embodying the ultimate expression of the thirsting deer, separated from the Father for the sake of the atonement.\n\n• The Man of Sorrows: Christ is the perfect fulfillment of the one whose soul is cast down. In the Garden of Gethsemane, He experienced the weight of the waves and billows of divine judgment passing over Him.\n\n• The Living God: The psalmist longs for the Living God; in the New Testament, we see Christ as the incarnation of that Life, making the presence of God accessible without the need for a physical Temple in Jerusalem.\n\n• The Great High Priest: As a Korahite psalm, it points to the necessity of a mediator who can lead the soul back to the house of God. Christ is the High Priest who leads the procession into the true heavenly sanctuary.",
