          "Alexander Maclaren highlights the audacity of the faith shown here. He observes that only someone with a deep, unshakable trust in God would dare to ask Him to wake up and explain Himself.",
          "H.C. Leupold suggests that the psalm demonstrates the reality of the hiddenness of God, a theme that resonates through the entire biblical record of the faithful who suffer without immediate explanation.",
          "Derek Kidner focuses on the integrity of the psalmist, noting that the claim of innocence in verses 17 through 21 is not a claim of sinless perfection but of covenantal loyalty.",
