        "content": "Hebrews 1:8-9: This is the most critical New Testament application, where the writer of Hebrews quotes Psalm 45:6-7 to prove the deity of Jesus Christ, asserting that the Father addresses the Son as God.\n\nJohn 1:14: The grace poured into the King’s lips in verse 2 finds fulfillment in Christ being full of grace and truth.\n\nRevelation 19:6-9: The marriage of the Lamb is the New Testament consummation of the wedding imagery introduced in this psalm.\n\nEphesians 5:25-32: Paul’s theology of Christ and the Church as a great mystery involving a husband and wife draws directly from the typology found in this royal wedding song.",
