        "content": "• Romans 2:21-23: This passage parallels the rebuke in Psalm 50:16-20 regarding those who teach the law and boast in God while breaking the very commandments they recite.\n\n• Romans 12:1: This reflects the transition from animal sacrifice mentioned in the psalm to the spiritual worship of offering one's body as a living sacrifice.\n\n• Mark 7:6-7: Jesus quotes the prophets to echo the sentiment of Psalm 50, stating that people honor God with their lips while their hearts are far from Him.\n\n• Hebrews 10:4-10: This New Testament passage clarifies that God took no pleasure in animal sacrifices for their own sake, pointing toward the ultimate and sufficient sacrifice of Jesus Christ.",
