        "title": "Christ in the Old Testament",
        "content": "• Christ is the true Hyssop and the true Sacrifice; where David recognized animal sacrifices were insufficient, Christ offered the one perfect sacrifice that actually takes away sin.\n\n• David’s prayer for a new creation of the heart points forward to the New Covenant work of Christ, who gives His followers a new heart and puts a new spirit within them (Ezekiel 36:26).\n\n• The theme of the broken and contrite heart is perfectly embodied in Christ, who was broken for our transgressions so that we might be healed.\n\n• As the Son of David, Christ is the righteous King who stands in the gap for His people, ensuring that the walls of the spiritual Zion are built and maintained through His intercession.",
