          "Matthew Henry highlights that when David says God is with those who uphold his soul, he acknowledges that while God may use human instruments for help, the power and grace come from God alone.",
          "Alexander Maclaren points out the rapid transition of the psalmist’s mood, noting that prayer has a miraculous power to bring the future deliverance into the present experience of the believer.",
          "Derek Kidner emphasizes that the freewill sacrifice in verse 6 is a voluntary expression of love that goes beyond the requirements of the law, signifying a heart that has been truly set free from fear.",
