          "Keil and Delitzsch point out that the Hebrew term for the River of God in verse 9 refers to the inexhaustible supply of rain from the heavens, contrasted with the finite irrigation systems of man.",
          "Matthew Henry focuses on the confidence of prayer, noting that because God is the Hearer of Prayer, all flesh has a warrant to come to Him, making the throne of grace the most accessible place in the universe.",
