        "title": "Brief Outline",
        "content": "Theme: The Glorious Majesty and Irresistible Judgment of the God of Zion.\n\nI. The Presence of God in His Sanctuary (Verses 1-3)\n\nA. His Name is known in Judah.\n\nB. His Dwelling is in Salem/Zion.\n\nC. His Victory over the weapons of war.\n\nII. The Power of God over the Nations (Verses 4-6)\n\nA. His Superiority over the mountains of prey.\n\nB. The Impotence of the mighty before Him.\n\nC. The Lethal Rebuke of the God of Jacob.\n\nIII. The Purpose of God in Judgment (Verses 7-9)\n\nA. The Dreadful Holiness of God.\n\nB. The Silence of the Earth before His decree.\n\nC. The Salvation of the afflicted.\n\nIV. The Praise of God from Human Wrath (Verses 10-12)\n\nA. The Sovereignty of God over human rebellion.\n\nB. The Vows due to the Terrible One.\n\nC. The Subjugation of the spirit of princes."
