        "content": "Hebrews 13:8: The psalmist asks if God’s mercy is clean gone forever. The New Testament answers this by declaring that Jesus Christ is the same yesterday, today, and forever, grounding the psalmist’s hope in the immutable nature of the Son.\n\nRomans 15:4: This verse affirms that the things written in the Law and the Psalms were written for our instruction and hope, justifying the psalmist’s method of looking back at the Exodus to find comfort for the present.\n\nRevelation 15:3: The Song of Moses and the Lamb echoes the redemptive themes of Psalm 77, where God’s power over the sea and the nations is the basis for the final victory of the saints.",
