        "content": "The Shepherd King: The psalm concludes with David being taken from the sheepfolds to shepherd Israel. This is a direct type of Jesus Christ, the Great Shepherd, who leads His people with integrity of heart and skillful hands (verse 72).\n\nThe Rock: The mention of God splitting the rocks to give water in the desert (verse 15) points toward Christ, the Spiritual Rock from whom the living water of the Spirit flows.\n\nThe Bread of Heaven: The description of manna as the corn of heaven and angels’ food (verses 24-25) is the Old Testament backdrop for Christ’s discourse in John 6, where He identifies Himself as the true Bread from Heaven.\n\nThe Parabolic Teacher: By opening His mouth in parables, Christ identifies Himself as the ultimate Asaph, the one who explains the mysteries of God’s kingdom and the meaning of redemptive history.",
