        "content": "• Christ is the true and greater Temple who was destroyed by the hands of wicked men but raised in three days, transforming the site of defilement into a place of eternal victory.\n\n• He is the Good Shepherd who literally gave His life for the sheep of His pasture, fulfilling the protective role the psalmist pleads for in the final verse.\n\n• Jesus acts as the ultimate High Priest who intercedes for the former iniquities of His people, ensuring that their sins are not remembered against them.\n\n• The sighing of the prisoner and those appointed to death in verse 11 find their release in Christ, who came to proclaim liberty to the captives and to abolish the power of death.\n\n• Christ is the Vindicator of Gods name, who in His second coming will execute the final and perfect judgment upon the nations that refuse to acknowledge the Lord.",
