        "content": "• 2 Peter 3:8: The Apostle Peter directly echoes the temporal perspective of Psalm 90:4, stating that with the Lord one day is as a thousand years and a thousand years as one day.\n\n• James 4:14: The New Testament concept of life being a vapor that appears for a little time and then vanishes is a thematic development of Moses grass imagery.\n\n• Ephesians 5:16: Paul’s instruction to redeem the time because the days are evil serves as the practical application of numbering our days.\n\n• Hebrews 4:9: The eternal rest offered to the people of God fulfills the desire for a permanent dwelling place mentioned in verse 1.",
