        "title": "Brief Outline",
        "content": "Theme: The Appeal for Divine Vindication and the Certain Ruin of the Treacherous Adversary.\n\n1. The Complaint (Verses 1-5): David describes the unprovoked malice and lying tongues of his enemies.\n\n2. The Imprecation (Verses 6-20): A prophetic call for judicial retribution against the chief antagonist.\n\n3. The Supplication (Verses 21-25): A humble plea for God’s help based on the psalmist’s weakness and God’s name.\n\n4. The Confidence (Verses 26-31): A concluding vow of praise in anticipation of God’s deliverance and the shame of the accusers."
