        "title": "Brief Outline",
        "content": "Theme: The Transcendent God Who Stoops to the Lowly.\n\nI. The Universal Call to Praise (Verses 1-3)\n\nA. The subjects of praise: Servants of the Lord.\n\nB. The duration of praise: Now and forever.\n\nC. The scope of praise: From east to west.\n\nII. The Incomparable Majesty of God (Verses 4-6)\n\nA. His exaltation over nations and heavens.\n\nB. His unique dwelling in the heights.\n\nC. His voluntary condescension to observe the creation.\n\nIII. The Compassionate Mercy of God (Verses 7-9)\n\nA. His intervention for the destitute (the dust and ash heap).\n\nB. His exaltation of the lowly to nobility.\n\nC. His restoration of domestic joy for the barren."
