        "content": "1. Matthew 5:17-18: Jesus declares that not one jot or tittle shall pass from the Law, echoing the psalmist’s claim in verse 89 that the Word is settled in heaven.\n\n2. John 1:1: The Davar (Word) that the psalmist loves is revealed in the New Testament as the Logos, the person of Jesus Christ.\n\n3. Romans 7:22: Paul’s statement that he delights in the law of God in his inner man is a direct thematic parallel to the psalmist’s repeated cries of delight in the statutes.\n\n4. Romans 10:4: Christ is the end of the law for righteousness, fulfilling the longing for perfect obedience expressed throughout the 176 verses.\n\n5. James 1:25: The perfect law of liberty mentioned by James reflects the psalmist’s view that the Word provides a spacious path for the feet (verse 45).",
