        "content": "1. Christ is the only human being who ever lived out Psalm 119 perfectly, as He was the Living Word who delighted to do the Father's will without exception.\n\n2. Verse 105 calls the Word a lamp and a light; Jesus identifies Himself in the Gospel of John as the Light of the World, the ultimate guide for the soul.\n\n3. The psalmist frequently prays for God to open his eyes to see wondrous things; Christ is the One who opened the eyes of the disciples on the road to Emmaus to see Himself in the Law and the Prophets.\n\n4. The suffering and persecution described in the psalm point to the Man of Sorrows who was despised and rejected by rulers, yet remained faithful to the Father’s commands.\n\n5. The final verse of the psalm (verse 176) confesses a tendency to wander like a lost sheep; this points to the necessity of Christ as the Good Shepherd who comes to seek and save that which was lost.",
