        "title": "Christ in the Old Testament",
        "content": "Christ is the ultimate realization of the Plenteous Redemption mentioned in verse 7. The Hebrew word feda implies a ransoming or buying back, which Christ accomplished on the cross.\n\nThe standing mentioned in verse 3 is only possible because Christ stood in the place of the sinner under the judgment of God, allowing us to stand clothed in His righteousness.\n\nThe waiting of the watchmen in verse 6 prefigures the expectant waiting for the First and Second Comings of Christ, the true Morning Star who ends the night of sin.\n\nAs the High Priest, Christ is the One who intercedes from the depths of human suffering, having entered the deepest depths of death to bring us to the heights of God’s presence.",
