        "content": "• Acts 2:30: Peter explicitly identifies the oath mentioned in Psalm 132:11 as a prophecy fulfilled in the resurrection of Jesus Christ, who sits on David’s throne.\n\n• Luke 1:32-33: The Angel Gabriel quotes the essence of this Psalm when announcing to Mary that the Lord God will give Jesus the throne of His father David.\n\n• Acts 7:46: Stephen’s speech before the Sanhedrin references David’s desire to find a tabernacle for the God of Jacob, citing the historical impetus of this Psalm.\n\n• Revelation 1:5: The description of Christ as the Prince of the kings of the earth reflects the promise in verse 18 that His crown shall flourish.",
