        "content": "• Christ is the ultimate Dwelling Place of God, the true Tabernacle who became flesh to dwell among men, fulfilling the longing for a place of rest expressed in verses 5 and 13.\n\n• The Horn of David mentioned in verse 17 is a direct Messianic title for Christ, representing His kingly authority and saving power.\n\n• The Lamp ordained for the Anointed One finds its reality in Christ as the Light of the World, ensuring that the testimony of God never goes dark in the house of David.\n\n• The eternal nature of the throne promised in verse 12 is only possible through the sinless life and indestructible life of Jesus, as earthly kings failed to keep the covenant conditions.",
