        "content": "• Jesus Christ is the quintessential Servant of the Lord who frequently spent His nights in prayer on the mountains, fulfilling the role of the night watchman interceding for His people.\n\n• The lifting of hands in the sanctuary points to Christ, who lifted His hands to bless His disciples at His ascension, securing the eternal blessing for His church (Luke 24:50).\n\n• Christ is the Creator of heaven and earth mentioned in verse 3, the eternal Logos through whom all things were made and through whom all blessing flows.\n\n• As the true High Priest, Christ remains in the heavenly sanctuary to ensure that the blessing of the Father rests upon the church continually.",
