          "John Calvin highlights the doctrine of justification by faith latent in verse 2. He argues that David voluntarily strips himself of all merit so that he may find favor in God's mercy alone. Calvin emphasizes that the righteousness of God here refers to His consistency in keeping His promises.",
          "Derek Kidner observes the shift from the first half of the psalm (despair) to the second half (dependence). He notes that the word for servant (ebed) in verses 2 and 12 provides the bookends for the prayer, indicating David's total submission to the Divine Will.",
